### Taskade nailed their execution in iOS

Atleast the parts I care about.

Things they nailed

- Clicking on a block, doesnt bring the keyboard, it first highlights it and a second tap converts to edit mode

- Typing automatically keeps the editor in center. When typing you can press enter and the view will scroll for you, keeping the in center. If you try to edit something on the edge, it automatically scrolls it into position.

# KB management

## Dynamic pages

Pitch: Imagine a page which is basically a glorified search for all the blocks which shows an interactive list of all the matches of a tag. You can go there see all the places tag:obsidian is used, make changes, see where the block is used etc.

- One problem would be on how to link bigger sections, for example this document is under the h1 `kb management`, or so does it look to a human. I think the easiest solution will be to do these on the fly, i.e. dynamically calculate them. Since they are just pointers and visual references, code can simply calculate them.

## Linking

- **Backlinks** There is this whole category of **backlinks** and people fetishize about it. The idea is that if you link a page, that page shows backlink to whatever page linked it. here is a [tweet](https://twitter.com/notionhq/status/1306677709263630336?s=21) from notion to give a gist.

  - Obisidian supports it, and notion started doing it too. I guess it was thing roam started.
